│ Given the complexity and the evidence, I believe the safest fix is to modify the `isDeadRecipe` function to not remove recipes that correspond to comparison instructions used in branch  │
│ conditions, even if they appear to have no users.                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ But how can we identify such recipes? We can check if the underlying instruction is a comparison that was used as a branch condition in the original loop.                                │
